&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;The Business Development and Partnerships team helps plan Waymo&#39;s dynamic future and drive the company&#39;s go-to-market strategy. We work cross-functionally and leverage quantitative and qualitative analysis to build forward-looking partnerships that deliver on Waymo&#39;s strategic business objectives. As a member of this entrepreneurial and results-oriented team, you will have a significant impact on defining, developing and executing Waymo&#39;s commercial deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Head of Business Development &amp;amp; Strategic Partnerships, Commercial Growth.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ビジネス開発チームおよびパートナーシップ チームは、Waymo のダイナミックな未来構想と市場開拓戦略の推進を担っています。部門横断的に活動し、定量的および定性的な分析を駆使して、Waymo の戦略的なビジネス目標を達成するための将来を見据えたパートナーシップを構築します。起業家精神にあふれ、結果を重視する本チームの一員として、Waymo の商用デプロイを実現するための重要サービスの定義、開発、実行において大きな影響を持つ役割を担当していただきます。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will / &lt;/strong&gt;業務内容:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute on a strategic partnerships strategy and plan to ensure successful go-to-market in Japan /&amp;nbsp;戦略的パートナーシップの立案と実行を通じて、日本における市場参入を成功に導く&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, create, negotiate and implement local strategic partnerships across the AV partnerships ecosystem, including operations and fleet partners, city and transit organizations, airports and other partners that support go-to-market, education/awareness, and growth/&amp;nbsp;運用およびフリートのパートナー、自治体や交通機関、空港、さらには市場認知の向上や成長を支援する各団体など、自律運転エコシステム全般にわたる地域の戦略的パートナーシップを特定、構築し、交渉から実装を行う&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Waymo Policy &amp;amp; Government Affairs and Legal teams to help influence national and local regulatory frameworks to enable testing and commercial deployment /&amp;nbsp;Waymo の政策および政府渉外チーム、法務チームと緊密に連携し、国や地域の規制の枠組みへの働きかけをサポートし、テストとおよび商用デプロイを可能にする&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can effectively represent Waymo in high stake external meetings with the government and strategic partners /&amp;nbsp;政府機関や戦略的パートナーとの重要な外部会議において、Waymo を代表して効果的な説明を行う&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a primary bridge between the Japan-based team and global teams at Waymo HQ, coordinating closely with partnerships efforts managed centrally and serving as a key voice representing local partnership interests, trends, and nuances.&amp;nbsp; Help Waymo achieve long term success in Japan with the most thoughtful approach - influence global thinking with a deep understanding of local nuances / 日本拠点と Waymo 本社のグローバル チームをつなぐ主要な窓口となり、本社が統括するパートナーシップ戦略と密に連携しつつ、国内におけるパートナーシップのニーズやトレンド、文化的背景を共有する。日本特有の市場環境や習慣への深い理解に基づき、グローバル戦略への反映を行うことで、Waymo が日本で長期的な成功を収めるための最適かつ配慮あるアプローチを支援する&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with teams across time zones to define strategy, solve complex problems, execute business initiatives, create work plans, lead analyses, develop and communicate final recommendations to move partnerships forward and ensure their ongoing success /&amp;nbsp;異なるタイムゾーンのチームと連携して戦略を定義し、複雑な課題解決やビジネス イニシアチブの実行、作業計画の策定から分析の主導を担う。また、パートナーシップを前進させて継続的な成功を確実にするための最終提言の作成および伝達を行う&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Have / 必要な条件/経験:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of work experience, including 5+ years in business development or strategic partnerships in the technology, transportation and/or mobility sector /&amp;nbsp;8 年以上の実務経験。そのうち 5 年以上は、テクノロジー、運輸、モビリティ分野における事業開発または戦略的パートナーシップの領域の経験であること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full business proficiency in both Japanese and English language (verbal and written) and the ability to cross-contextualize and communicate effectively across both Japanese and US cultures and styles /&amp;nbsp;日本語および英語における高いビジネス語学力（会話および読み書き）。日米両方の文化やスタイルの違いを深く理解し、文脈を補完しながら効果的にコミュニケーションを図る能力&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience structuring and negotiating strategic partnership agreements /&amp;nbsp;戦略的パートナーシップ契約の構築および交渉における実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading and influencing a cross-functional team, particularly a team that includes policy, operations, product, marketing and finance stakeholders /&amp;nbsp;部門横断的なチーム（特に政策、運用、プロダクト、マーケティング、財務などのステークホルダーを含むチーム）を牽引し、組織に影響を与えた経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent practical experience /&amp;nbsp;学士号、またはそれに相当する実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Prefer / &lt;/strong&gt;望ましい条件/経験:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of the autonomous vehicle, ride hailing or broader mobility industries /&amp;nbsp;自律運転車、配車サービス、または幅広いモビリティ業界における深い知識&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of the Japanese business landscape, culture, and regulatory environment (especially in mobility or technology) /&amp;nbsp;日本のビジネス環境、文化、および規制環境（特にモビリティやテクノロジー分野）に関する深い知識&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in both US and Japanese companies /&amp;nbsp;米国企業および日本企業双方における勤務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience with international market entry, product launches, or scaling a new business /&amp;nbsp;国際市場への参入、プロダクト リリース、または新規事業の拡大に直接携わった経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide travel requirements (if applicable) / 出張について&lt;/strong&gt;（該当する場合）:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel will be required, around 10-20% of time /&amp;nbsp;業務時間の10〜20% 程度の出張が発生する場合があります&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo&#39;s Product Data Science team works cross-functionally with Engineering, Product and Operations to help the company make the most informed decisions using data. Our team collaborates on high-impact projects across the company — from driving quality and operational efficiency to market analysis and rider satisfaction scores — we help to safely and efficiently scale the Waymo Driver. We are data-driven, curious, open-minded, and adapt quickly to new information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role follows a hybrid work schedule and you will report to the Manager of Product Data Science.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Managers, Engineers, Program Managers to identify the right measurement for business performance, design and implement foundational data pipelines, and build the right reports and visualizations to drive insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop deep understanding of various metrics, datasets, and data sources in relation to the rich business and operational context across the entire product landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain state of the art reporting infrastructure to enable continuous decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform advanced analytical modelling as necessary to help drive the right decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive a culture of excellence and help establish best practices within the broader data science team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in a related technical field or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to scope, structure, and solve ambiguous problems independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coding experience with Python and SQL to design and implement complex data pipelines following best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Statistical knowledge/data intuition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience interacting with senior leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the AV industry / Mapping / Ridesharing / Consumer Tech / People Analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$125,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$157,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo&#39;s Data Science team is an important part of our mission to develop safe and reliable autonomous driving technology. We use data analysis and leverage statistical expertise to evaluate and improve the Waymo Driver, focusing on areas like reliability, driving quality, and safety. Our work ensures that data-driven insights inform key aspects of Waymo&#39;s development process.&amp;nbsp; As a Business Intelligence Analyst, you will help build the data infrastructure behind reporting and analytics for some core pillars supported by the Waymo Data Science team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a Data Analyst in our Warsaw office, you will leverage advanced SQL and Business Intelligence tools to build state-of-the-art reporting infrastructure (data pipelines, dashboards) to ensure decision making within one of:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Waymo Driving Quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Waymo Safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Waymo Reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write high quality data pipelines with clear definitions to ensure consistency of metrics across the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, define, and govern key performance indicators (KPIs) and core metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Data Science, Engineering, Operations, Product, and Regulatory teams to allow accurate reporting to several audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare content and communicate to Waymo leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run deep analyses into data trends observed to drive partner team goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in a Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Analyst, or similar quantitative role within a tech-forward environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced SQL proficiency – you are an expert at writing high-performance queries, including window functions, UDFs, and complex joins to manipulate large-scale datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Engineering mindset – experience managing and querying extremely large datasets (BigQuery, Redshift, or similar) and building scalable data pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Visualization &amp;amp; Storytelling – a proven track record of building intuitive, &quot;executive-ready&quot; dashboards in modern BI tools (e.g., Tableau, Looker, or Data Studio).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Infrastructure Management – expertise in building and maintaining data infrastructure for large organizations, ensuring a clean separation between development and production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder Influence – the ability to translate complex data trends into actionable insights for Engineering, Product, and Leadership teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive Problem Solving – demonstrates the initiative and foresight to identify business needs before they become critical bottlenecks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Waymo’s Product Data Science team works cross-functionally with Engineering, Product and Operations to help the company make the most informed decisions using data. Our team collaborates on high-impact projects across the company — from driving quality and operational efficiency to market analysis and rider satisfaction scores — we help to safely and efficiently scale the Waymo Driver. We are data-driven, curious, open-minded, and adapt quickly to new information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
