&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Digital Transformation team defines and builds the business IT architecture that supports the commercial operation of Waymo&#39;s autonomous vehicle fleet. The team stands at the intersection of supply chain, finance, operations and IT; through creative architecture, expertise and attention to detail, it ensures that Waymo has world-class capabilities across all its business processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Senior Manager, Supply Chain &amp;amp; GTM Systems&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create the “to-be” technology footprint, develop solutions roadmap and phased implementation approach to achieve strategic business objectives within Supply Chain and Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on setup and support of SAP MM, PP and EAM/PM processes like MRP, Production Orders, Demand Management, Procurement, Inventory Management, Maintenance Orders and other sub processes like BOM, routing, work centers, Production versions, activity types, maintenance types, Maintenance planning, functional locations, Operations, task lists, Equipment Master, Maintenance Plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on customization and configuration of SAP S/4 HANA and other boundary systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead functional tasks and deliverables including: process definition and re-engineering, requirements gathering, fit/gap analysis, functional design, testing, training, reporting, support, and continuous improvement of business applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on creating Business requirements document, Functional specification document, Technical specifications document, process flow diagrams, user stories, and test cases to support the design and development of a wide variety of business system tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional collaboration to deliver successful products and/or features, including process, and change management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or equivalent years of work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years in two of the five SAP modules - Order to Cash, Supply Planning, Materials Management, Production Planning and Enterprise Asset Management experience in a full cycle implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and collaboration skills with a proven track record of implementing impactful cross-function programs in a complex organizational environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;APICS Certifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SAP Certifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;((Remote jobs only - Please note that Waymo may not be able to employ remotely in all locations. Please speak with your recruiter about your preferred location for remote work when you begin the interview process.))&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$158,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$200,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local Market Leadership and Partner Support: &lt;/strong&gt;As an early operations hire in London, ensure our Fleet Operating Partner is well supported by facilitating in-person touchpoints, feedback loops, and internal advocacy to operations and engineering teams to unblock their issues and empower their success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Daily Operations Monitoring and Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Actively oversee daily autonomous vehicle operations across all markets in real time. Monitor live operational data to detect and respond to immediate issues impacting AV performance. Investigate the “why” when issues occur, escalating to and collaborating with local teams and global operations for timely intervention and with product / engineering for long term solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Management &amp;amp; Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Directly manage performance for global commercial and testing operations, while providing hands-on guidance and real-time coaching to Waymo’s partners and vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real-Time Reporting and Communication: &lt;/strong&gt;Regularly update key stakeholders on team activities, operational status, and any incidents. Ensure accurate and prompt communication with global operations and other teams for effective coordination and rapid response. Manage complex stakeholder relationships across multiple teams, including local operations, systems operations, product development, engineering, and others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safety and Performance Compliance: &lt;/strong&gt;Actively monitor and enforce Waymo’s safety standards and performance benchmarks. Address deviations promptly to ensure consistent, reliable, and safe operations across all markets. Lead safety / risk audits and partner with safety leads to implement risk-reduction strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement Feedback:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Proactively generate ideas to drive continuous improvement in daily operations - even if the problem is ambiguous - and take full ownership of the solution. Report recurring issues and recommend potential adjustments to procedures, collaborating with cross-functional teams to enhance operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 6 years experience in consulting, technical operations,&amp;nbsp; product operations, technical account management,&amp;nbsp; vendor management / advocacy, or other related roles that blend strong technical know-how with stakeholder engagement to uncover problems and work cross functionally with technical teams to build solutions to those problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven strong data-driven decision-making skills and comfort working with relevant technologies for continuous operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross functional collaboration experience: ability to hear issues from teams in person, translate those problems into clear problem statements, and work with global engineering teams to resolve those issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some flexibility in scheduling to ensure business continuity with AMER and EMEA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in business, supply chain, operations research, engineering, or other technical / operational studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with working with non-local product / engineering teams (especially in United States)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years experience with real-time operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with autonomous vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multi-lingual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience overseeing and supporting operational teams, including monitoring performance and ensuring adherence to protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience directly guiding large groups of people in a real-time operational setting, providing clear instructions and ensuring performance and safety standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onboarding: Travel to SF, USA and Phoenix USA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Summits: Travel to Phoenix, USA (~once or twice a year)&amp;nbsp; for a team summit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potential travel to other markets in the EMEA region on an ad-hoc basis as we launch / scale new markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level.&amp;nbsp; Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;£88,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;£95,000 GBP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate./ Waymo Operations の目的は、Waymo Driver を世界中にお届けすることです。私たちは世界初かつ最先端の自律走行車両と、その運用プラットフォームの構築および拡大を担っているグローバル チームです。部品の調達から顧客の管理まで、Waymo Driver を大規模かつ緻密に展開することで Waymo の価値創造を行っています。また、Waymo ではお互いに協力し合い、称え合う文化を築いています。チームメンバーそれぞれのバックグラウンドや視点、経験を尊重し、Waymo が事業を展開するコミュニティへさらに貢献するため、全員が自由にアイデアを提案できるようサポートし、奨励しています。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:/業務内容:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local Market Leadership and Partner Support: &lt;/strong&gt;As the first operations hire in Japan, ensure our Fleet Operating Partner is well supported by facilitating in-person touchpoints, feedback loops, and internal advocacy to operations and engineering teams to unblock their issues and empower their success./ &lt;strong&gt;ローカル マーケットにおけるリーダーシップとパートナー支援&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: &lt;/strong&gt;日本におけるオペレーション部門の最初のメンバーとして、フリート オペレーション パートナーを手厚くサポートする。対面でのタッチポイント、フィードバック ループの構築、社内のオペレーション チームとエンジニアリング チームへの働きかけを通じて、パートナーの課題を解決し、その成功を支援する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Daily Operations Monitoring and Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Actively oversee daily autonomous vehicle operations across all markets in real time. Monitor live operational data to detect and respond to immediate issues impacting AV performance. Investigate the “why” when issues occur, escalating to and collaborating with local teams and global operations for timely intervention and with product / engineering for long term solutions./&lt;strong&gt;グローバルな日常業務の監視とサポート: &lt;/strong&gt;全市場における自律運転車の日常運用をリアルタイムで積極的に監視する。ライブ運用データをモニタリングして、車両のパフォーマンスに影響を与えるような緊急を要する課題を検出し、対応を行う。問題発生時にはその「原因（なぜ）」を調査し、現地チームおよびグローバル オペレーションにエスカレーションしてタイムリーな介入を行うとともに、プロダクト / エンジニアリング チームと連携して長期的な解決策を策定する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Management &amp;amp; Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Directly manage performance for global commercial and testing operations, while providing hands-on guidance and real-time coaching to Waymo’s partners and Partners./ &lt;strong&gt;パフォーマンス管理とサポート: &lt;/strong&gt;グローバルな商用運用およびテスト業務におけるパフォーマンスを直接管理する。同時に Waymo のパートナーや提携先に、実践的なガイダンスとリアルタイムのコーチングを提供する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real-Time Reporting and Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Regularly update key stakeholders on team activities, operational status, and any incidents. Ensure accurate and prompt communication with global operations and other teams for effective coordination and rapid response. Manage complex stakeholder relationships across multiple teams, including local operations, systems operations, product development, engineering, and others./ &lt;strong&gt;リアルタイム レポーティングおよびコミュニケーション:&lt;/strong&gt; チームの活動状況、運用の状況、インシデントに関する情報を主要なステークホルダーへ定期的に報告する。グローバル オペレーションや関連チームとの正確かつ迅速なコミュニケーションを徹底し、円滑な調整と迅速な対応を行う。ローカル オペレーションやシステム運用、プロダクト開発、エンジニアリングなど、複数の部門が関わる複雑なステークホルダー間の関係を調整する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safety and Performance Compliance: &lt;/strong&gt;Actively monitor and enforce Waymo’s safety standards and performance benchmarks. Address deviations promptly to ensure consistent, reliable, and safe operations across all markets. Lead safety / risk audits and partner with safety leads to implement risk-reduction strategies./ &lt;strong&gt;安全性とパフォーマンスに関するコンプライアンス: &lt;/strong&gt;Waymo の安全基準およびパフォーマンス ベンチマークを積極的にモニタリングし、遵守を徹底する。基準からの逸脱に対しては速やかに対処し、すべての市場において運用の一貫性、信頼性、安全性を担保する。また、安全性 / リスク監査を主導し、安全監督責任者と連携してリスク軽減戦略を実行する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement Feedback: &lt;/strong&gt;Proactively generate ideas to drive continuous improvement in daily operations - even if the problem is ambiguous - and take full ownership of the solution. Report recurring issues and recommend potential adjustments to procedures, collaborating with cross-functional teams to enhance operational efficiency. / &lt;strong&gt;継続的な改善とフィードバック: &lt;/strong&gt;課題があいまいな状況であっても、日々の業務における継続的な改善を推進するため、積極的にアイデアを創出し、解決に向けてオーナーシップを持って取り組む。繰り返し発生する問題を報告し、プロセスの最適化を提案し、部門横断的なチームと連携して運用の効率化を高める。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:/必要な条件/経験:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 6 years experience in consulting, technical operations,&amp;nbsp; product operations, technical account management,&amp;nbsp; Partner management / advocacy, or other related roles that blend strong technical know-how with stakeholder engagement to uncover problems and work cross functionally with technical teams to build solutions to those problems./ コンサルティング、技術運用、プロダクト運用、テクニカル アカウント マネジメント、パートナー管理 / アドボカシー、またはそれらに関連する領域における 6 年以上の実務経験。高度な技術的ノウハウとステークホルダーを巻き込む力を備え、課題を発見し、技術チームと部門横断的な連携によるソリューション構築をリードした経験を有すること。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in both English and Japanese / 英語と日本語の両方に堪能であること。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven strong data-driven decision-making skills and comfort working with relevant technologies for continuous operations. /データドリブン型の優れた意思決定能力を備え、継続的な運用のための関連技術に精通していること。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross functional collaboration experience: ability to hear issues from teams in person, translate those problems into clear problem statements, and work with global engineering teams to resolve those issues./ 部門横断的な連携経験: チームから課題を直接ヒアリングし、それらを明確な問題定義として言語化できる能力。また、グローバルのエンジニアリング チームと協力して課題を解決する能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some flexibility in scheduling to ensure business continuity with AMER and EMEA /AMER および EMEA との事業継続を確保するための柔軟なスケジュール調整能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:/望ましい経験/スキル:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in business, supply chain, operations research, engineering, or other technical / operational studies. / ビジネス、サプライ チェーン、オペレーションズ リサーチ、エンジニアリング、またはその他技術 / 運用研究分野における学士号&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with working with non-local product / engineering teams (especially in United States) / 海外のプロダクト / エンジニアリング チーム（特に米国拠点）との連携経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years experience with real-time operations / リアルタイム オペレーションにおける 3 年以上の実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with autonomous vehicles / 自律走行車に関連する経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience overseeing and supporting operational teams, including monitoring performance and ensuring adherence to protocols. / パフォーマンス監視やプロトコル遵守の徹底など、運用チームの監督およびサポートの経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience directly guiding large groups of people in a real-time operational setting, providing clear instructions and ensuring performance and safety standards. / リアルタイムの運用環境において大規模なグループを直接指揮し、的確な指示を通じてパフォーマンスおよび安全基準を担保した経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel: / 出張について:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onboarding: Travel to SF, USA and Phoenix USA / オンボーディング: 米国サンフランシスコおよび米国フェニックスへの出張&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Summits: Travel to Phoenix, USA (~once or twice a year)&amp;nbsp; for a team summit / サミット: チームサミットの参加のため米国フェニックスへの出張（年に 1～2 回程度）&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potential travel to other markets in the EMEA region on an ad-hoc basis as we launch / scale new markets / 新規市場の立ち上げや事業拡大に伴い、EMEA 地域の各拠点への出張が発生する可能性あり&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Waymo may not be able to employ remotely in all locations. Please speak with your recruiter about your preferred location for remote work when you begin the interview process. / Waymo では、採用地によってリモート勤務が適用されない場合がありますのでご了承ください。ご希望のリモート勤務場所については、選考プロセスの開始時に採用担当者までご相談ください。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;At Waymo Insurance, you will work on the cutting edge of emerging risk and related issues surrounding our transformational autonomous driving technology and help drive our business lines forward from technology ideation through scaled commercial deployment. We partner with our legal, public policy, safety, security and privacy experts to evaluate and manage risks for the autonomous driving world to come, advising on insurance trends, evaluating and quantifying product liability, auto, cyber and related risks to ensure we build the appropriate risk and insurance frameworks to support and protect our users around the world. We collaborate with our business development, product partnership, strategy and operations teams in the execution of our business plans to ensure the company&#39;s interests are well protected from existing, new and emerging risks. We support the legal, policy and regulatory teams as they optimize our exposure in line with our risk appetite through the review of contracts, evaluation and shaping of emerging law and regulation at both the state and federal level. And we anticipate, quantify and mitigate emerging risk by maintaining active relationships and frequent contact with insurance and AV industry partners.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Claims Manager within the Risk &amp;amp; Insurance Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and triage claims that are presented against Waymo to understand the exposure, how to respond to those claims and how best to protect Waymo, both through claim handling/payment and defense.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide oversight to claim handling partners to ensure that claims are handled within SLAs and meet Waymo’s expectations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional interactions with riders and customers - showing empathy, understanding, and having the knowledge to assist in a variety of situations and manners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help to create strategies, tools and processes (documenting all) to handle the unique nature of claims in an autonomous vehicle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years insurance claim experience (preferably in Auto Liability and General Liability)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on claim projects and both creating and documenting claim processes but also identifying bottlenecks in processes and being able to escalate and/or provide recommendations for enhancement/improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience relative to claim handling, to include, but not be limited to the ability to investigate and triage complex claims, with key issue identification skills, and claim evaluation and negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced communication skills which are critical to building consensus across areas of influence (external and/or internal relationships), team, and/or matrix environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to manage a large inventory of claims, maintain SLAs and provide oversight to claim handling partners (whether carriers, TPAs, or otherwise).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with US and International markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPCU, AIC and/or SCLA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimal to none&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$125,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$157,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;As a member of the Public Affairs team, you will be at the forefront of bringing autonomous driving technology to the public. Our focus is implementing advocacy, grassroots, and grasstops campaigns to drive acceptance and adoption of our life-saving technology. We work directly with key third party groups and influencers to educate the public on the safety benefits of Waymo’s fully autonomous driving technology. Internally, our efforts support the innovative work of engineering, product, safety, and external engagement teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Public Affairs Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect community strategies:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and execute local engagement plans in a variety of urban markets to ensure both Waymo and our local infrastructure projects are understood and supported.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closely partner&lt;/strong&gt; with a variety of cross-functional internal teams and local consultants for both strategic planning and tactical execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mitigate friction:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively identify potential community pain points—such as construction noise or traffic—and implement creative solutions to maintain neighborhood understanding and harmony.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage multi-channel outreach:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage a variety of engagements - including potentially door-knocking campaigns, town halls, digital updates, and &quot;coffee chats&quot; – to keep residents informed and heard.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translate complexity:&lt;/strong&gt; Turn technical infrastructure jargon into clear, relatable stories about how Waymo serves, partners with, and invests in local communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community liaison:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as a liaison between Waymo and key neighborhood stakeholders, including non-profits and small business owners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ground game experience:&lt;/strong&gt; At least 5 years in public affairs, community organizing, or local government relations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional emotional intelligence:&lt;/strong&gt; The ability to remain calm and empathetic in high-pressure situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project management excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience managing multiple simultaneous projects across different time zones, city jurisdictions, and with the input of several cross-functional internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stellar communication skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional writing and public speaking skills, with an ability to tailor your message to everyone from a city councilor to a local shopkeeper.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ability to travel:&lt;/strong&gt; A willingness to travel to be physically present in the neighborhoods where the work is happening.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Autonomous Vehicle (AV) or mobility background:&lt;/strong&gt; Prior experience in the mobility, transit, or logistics sectors, particularly helping communities navigate the transition to new technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local urban experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Specific experience working with diverse urban demographics and a deep understanding of the unique social and political fabrics of major metro areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crisis &amp;amp; issues management:&lt;/strong&gt; A proven track record of managing active neighborhood friction, such as construction mitigation, zoning disputes, or high-profile public feedback sessions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crisis communication tools:&lt;/strong&gt; Proficiency with CRM tools (like Salesforce or StakeTracker) and digital engagement platforms to track community sentiment and manage outreach data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative storytelling:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience using visual aids, maps, or digital media to simplify complex infrastructure projects for a non-technical audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Established local networks:&lt;/strong&gt; Existing relationships with urban planning groups, accessibility advocates, or business improvement districts (BIDs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multilingual capabilities:&lt;/strong&gt; Fluency in a second language (e.g., Spanish or Cantonese) to ensure inclusive outreach in linguistically diverse neighborhoods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel requirements&lt;/strong&gt; (if applicable):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role requires up to 30% travel to be physically present in the neighborhoods and markets where we are opening infrastructure to support our growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$158,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$200,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Waymo&#39;s cars may be self-driving, but its construction projects are steered by experts like you. Safety is our foundation and is at the heart of everything we do. As Waymo&#39;s Construction Project Executive you will be responsible for site due diligence, design oversight, permitting and build out of a variety of locations across industrial, automotive service and EV charging typologies for Waymo in an extremely fast paced environment with a high degree of ambiguity. At every turn, process excellence, collaboration, and detailed cross-org communications are critical.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for site due diligence, negotiations of transaction work letter documents, permitting, design oversight and build out of a variety of locations across ev charging and automotive service center typologies that include electrical utility upgrades&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize and present executive-level business cases for capital investment strategies across a diverse portfolio of projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships across the business and act as liaison to ensure alignment between investments and the portfolio strategies. Effectively communicate expectations, requirements and status of deals to key business stakeholders, building a culture of speed, flexibility and frugality for solutioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closely collaborate with GPS peers as well as Waymo legal, finance and procurement teams in order to deliver highly successful projects as well as security, network and other partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate and execute processes and tools to ensure the complete cycle from site search due diligence through deal execution to the first day of business is completed consistently and predictably, managing ever-changing variety of internal initiatives and projects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, innovate and implement relevant systems of metrics to plan, manage and measure performance pertaining to the project delivery process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of real estate project management of industrial operations, automobile service and charging of at least 500,000 square feet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading large scale real estate construction projects, orchestrating teams of project managers, architects, contractors, consultants and attorneys through deal flows at values of $20M each and greater&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional project delivery skills, including the ability to gather relevant jurisdictional limitations and roadblocks, as well as communicate recommendations effectively to various stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced financial reporting and analysis acumen as well as budget management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing and implementing process improvements to streamline the full project delivery cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of proven objective analysis, having delivering projects in an atmosphere where speed, flexibility and frugality are the norm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business relationship management expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in construction management, architecture, engineering, real estate, business administration or finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automotive and/or rideshare sector interest, if not experience&lt;/li&gt;
