&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Waymo Safety team works to promote and help to continuously improve the safety of Waymo&#39;s fully autonomous driving technology. Our experts develop safety goals and strategies, and conduct safety engineering analyses to ensure safety is being considered throughout the design and development of our vehicles. The team develops and promotes safety strategies and policies for autonomous vehicles for its work with regulatory authorities, lawmakers, law enforcement and public and non-profit organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Waymo Safety チームは、Waymo の完全自動運転技術の安全性の向上と継続的改善に取り組んでいます。Waymo の専門家は、安全目標と戦略を策定するとともに、安全工学分析を実施し、車両の設計および開発のすべての工程で安全性が考慮されるよう取り組んでいます。チームは、規制当局、立法機関、法執行機関、公共団体、非営利団体と連携するため、自動運転車に関する安全戦略およびポリシーの策定と推進を行っています。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this role you will be hybrid based in Tokyo and report into our Head of Resilience and Incident Management. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;この役割はロンドンを拠点とするハイブリッド勤務となり、レジリエンスおよびインシデント管理責任者にレポートします。&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will / 業務内容&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a native Japanese speaker, also proficient in English. / 日本語を母語とし、英語にも堪能であること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain primary contact with Emergency Services at management and executive levels in current and future areas of operation. / 現在および将来のオペレーション領域において、管理職および経営幹部レベルの緊急サービスとの主な連絡窓口を確立し、維持します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, present, and certify additional Emergency Services Ambassadors (ESAs) and Emergency Services stakeholders on Waymo&#39;s mission, technology, and industry concerns. / Waymo の使命、テクノロジー、業界の懸念事項について、追加の緊急サービス アンバサダー（ESA）および緊急サービス関係者の設計、提示、認定を行います。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide oversight, review, and guidance to Emergency Services training teams and act as the final source of truth for Emergency Services questions. / 緊急サービス トレーニング チームに対して監督、レビュー、指導を行い、緊急サービスに関する質問について最終的な公式見解を示す責任を担います。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Waymo at Emergency Services events, panels, and industry events. / 緊急サービス イベント、パネル ディスカッション、業界イベントで Waymo を代表します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as Waymo’s on the ground representative during emergency events and coordinate with local emergency services and local authorities. / 緊急事態発生時に Waymo の現地代表として活動し、地域の緊急サービスおよび地方当局と連携します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have / 必須条件:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of service in Japan’s emergency services (Police, Fire &amp;amp; Rescue, or Ambulance Service) / 日本の緊急サービス（警察、消防および救助、または救急サービス）での 10 年以上の勤務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of Japan’s legal frameworks, emergency protocols, and community engagement strategies. /&amp;nbsp;日本の法的枠組み、緊急時対応プロトコル、コミュニティ関与戦略に関する深い理解&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and presentation skills, capable of engaging diverse audiences. /&amp;nbsp;多様な聴衆を惹きつけることのできる、優れたコミュニケーション能力およびプレゼンテーション能力&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong understanding of the specific nuances and sensitivities of Emergency Services communities in Japan. / 日本の緊急サービス コミュニティ特有のニュアンスや配慮を深く理解していること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to establish and maintain a professional presence at executive and command staff levels. /&amp;nbsp;経営幹部および指揮スタッフレベルにおいて、専門的な信頼関係を確立し、維持できる能力&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative mindset and the ability to work effectively with legal and other internal teams. / 協調的な姿勢を有し、法務チームやその他の社内チームと効果的に連携できる能力&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer / 歓迎条件:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 7 years in a leadership or management position within one of Japan’s principal emergency services. / 日本の主要な緊急サービス機関のいずれかにおいて、指導的立場または管理職として少なくとも 7 年の実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience establishing organizational presence in new geographic locations. / 新しい地域において組織のプレゼンスを確立した経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with autonomous vehicle technology and its implications for emergency services. / 自動運転車技術およびそれが緊急サービスに与える影響に関する知識&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of policy development related to emergency management. / 緊急事態管理に関する政策立案の実績&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a role requiring significant public speaking and stakeholder engagement. / 重要な公の場での発言や利害関係者との関与を必要とする職務の経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in rapidly scaling and complex operational environments. / 急速に拡大する複雑な運用環境での業務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Travel Requirements / 出張要件:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;~20% travel (Domestic &amp;amp; International) /&amp;nbsp;約 20% の出張（国内および海外）&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please Note: This role works with sensitive content or situations and may be exposed to graphic, controversial, and/or upsetting topics or content. / &lt;strong&gt;注: &lt;/strong&gt;この職務ではデリケートなコンテンツや状況を扱うことがあり、刺激的、物議を醸す、または不快感を伴うトピックやコンテンツに接する可能性があります。&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to the Director of Waymo Product Operations &amp;amp; Planning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design &amp;amp; Implementation: Develop and implement the necessary Quality Management System (QMS) policies, procedures, and documentation across Waymo&#39;s value chain. Specifically, this role concentrates on Hardware &amp;amp; Software Engineering, and supply chain for autonomous vehicles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design Control: Implement and monitor QMS processes related to Design Control (ISO 9001 Clause 8.3) for the &quot;Waymo Driver&quot; autonomous technology, ensuring requirements traceability, design reviews, verification, and validation activities align with the framework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Conformity: Ensure Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) processes conform to defined quality standards, covering planning, requirements gathering, development, and testing of software solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Change Management: Develop and audit robust Change Management protocols (ISO 9001/IATF 16949) for software releases, feature updates, and bug fixes to systematically plan, assess risks, verify effectiveness, and eliminate adverse effects of changes before deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supplier Quality Management: Collaborate with Supply Chain and Procurement to define and implement QMS requirements for suppliers, ensuring adherence to standards like IATF 16949 and verifying that components and services meet the highest standards of specification and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Risk &amp;amp; Issue Resolution (CAPA): Lead Root Cause Analysis (RCA) and administer the Corrective and Preventive Action (CAPA) system across the federated structure to address non-conformities related to hardware, tooling, and operational procedures, ensuring universal application of lessons learned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Engineering (Software, Mechanical, Electrical, Industrial), Computer Science, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of demonstrable experience developing, implementing, and auditing an enterprise-level Quality Management System (QMS) based on ISO 9001 and/or IATF 16949 and/or ISO Software standards in a regulated or safety-critical industry (e.g., Automotive, Aerospace), plus experience with ASPICE (Automotive Software Process Improvement and Capability determination)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in core quality methodologies, including Root Cause Analysis (RCA), Corrective and Preventive Action (CAPA), and Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with functional safety standards like ISO 26262 (Functional Safety) or ISO 21448 (SOTIF), or cybersecurity standards like ISO/SAE 21434.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience integrating QMS processes with Software Engineering SDLC and managing quality for complex, rapidly evolving software platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with hardware quality control (e.g., tooling, calibration, maintenance processes) within a fleet or manufacturing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with data analysis tools (e.g., Python, SQL, Tableau) to manipulate, visualize, and report on quality performance data collected from decentralized operational units and the eQMS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to travel to vendor/partner sites 5-10% of time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$152,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$192,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;The Waymo Safety team works to promote and help to continuously improve the safety of Waymo’s fully autonomous driving technology. Our experts develop safety goals and strategies, and conduct safety engineering analyses to ensure safety is being considered throughout the design and development of our vehicles. The team develops and promotes safety strategies and policies for autonomous vehicles for its work with regulatory authorities, lawmakers, law enforcement and public and non-profit organizations. Our Safety Team also helps advise on compliance with applicable environmental, health, and safety regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;In this role, you will work with other members of Waymo’s Safety team and with technical and non-technical partners across Waymo to identify and analyze issues that could impact the safety of Waymo’s fleet of autonomous vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead investigations into driverless events, employee safety concerns, and other potential issues that could pose risks to the safety of Waymo vehicles currently operating in the field. Work with other Waymo teams to develop solutions when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze data from Waymo vehicles to identify and assess trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Legal and other Waymo teams to respond to governmental investigations and legal claims.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help promote a positive safety culture throughout the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor of Science in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related technical degree and 5+ years work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with field safety or safety investigations in the form of accident reconstruction, failure analysis, safety-related investigations, and/or automotive defect investigation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical proficiency demonstrated through experience performing quantitative risk assessment, reliability analysis, and/or statistical data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self motivated and ability to network internally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;M.S. or Ph.D. in engineering or a related technical field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software familiarity in autonomy or machine learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with product liability principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in evaluating and ensuring regulatory compliance and/or interacting with regulators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with highly automated vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
