&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Waymo Safety team works to promote and help to continuously improve the safety of Waymo&#39;s fully autonomous driving technology. Our experts develop safety goals and strategies, and conduct safety engineering analyses to ensure safety is being considered throughout the design and development of our vehicles. The team develops and promotes safety strategies and policies for autonomous vehicles for its work with regulatory authorities, lawmakers, law enforcement and public and non-profit organizations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Waymo Safety チームは、Waymo の完全自動運転技術の安全性の向上と継続的改善に取り組んでいます。Waymo の専門家は、安全目標と戦略を策定するとともに、安全工学分析を実施し、車両の設計および開発のすべての工程で安全性が考慮されるよう取り組んでいます。チームは、規制当局、立法機関、法執行機関、公共団体、非営利団体と連携するため、自動運転車に関する安全戦略およびポリシーの策定と推進を行っています。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based in Tokyo, reporting to Waymo’s Senior Director, Safety based in California. As Waymo’s first Field Safety Engineer in Japan, you will serve as Waymo’s primary engineering/technical liaison with safety regulators in Japan, working closely with Waymo’s Policy, Legal, and other teams in Japan. You will also work with Waymo’s Field Safety team in the United States to identify and analyze issues that could impact the safety of Waymo’s fleet of autonomous vehicles, with a focus on issues specific to Waymo’s operations in Japan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;この役職は東京を拠点とし、カリフォルニアを拠点とする Waymo のシニア ディレクター（セーフティ）にレポートします。Waymo の日本における最初のフィールド セーフティ エンジニアとして、日本の Waymo のポリシー、法務、その他のチームと緊密に連携しながら、日本の安全規制当局に対する Waymo の主要なエンジニアリング / 技術連絡窓口として業務を行います。また、米国の Waymo のフィールド セーフティ チームと連携し、日本での Waymo のオペレーションに特有の課題に焦点を当てながら、Waymo の自動運転車フリートの安全性に影響を及ぼす可能性のある問題を特定し、分析します。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will / 業務内容&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a native Japanese speaker, also proficient in English /&amp;nbsp;日本語を母語とし、英語にも堪能であること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as Waymo’s primary engineering/technical liaison with automotive and traffic safety regulators in Japan, e.g. Ministry of Land, Infrastructure, Transport, and Tourism (MLIT) National Police Agency (NPA), and Tokyo Metropolitan Police Department (TMPD). You will work with Waymo’s Policy, Legal, and other teams to establish and maintain proactive outreach with these regulators and also respond to requests from regulators. / 国土交通省（MLIT）、警察庁（NPA）、警視庁（TMPD）など、日本の自動車および交通安全規制当局に対する Waymo の主要なエンジニアリング / 技術連絡窓口を務めます。Waymo のポリシー、法務、その他のチームと連携し、これらの規制当局との積極的な連携関係を確立および維持するとともに、規制当局からの要請にも対応します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will work with Waymo’s Field Safety team in the United States to identify and analyze issues that could impact the safety of Waymo’s fleet of autonomous vehicles, bringing your local Japan perspective to help identify and prioritize issues that could impact Waymo’s operations in Japan. / 米国の Waymo のフィールド セーフティ チームと連携して、Waymo の自動運転車フリートの安全性に影響を及ぼす可能性のある問題を特定して分析するとともに、日本に関する知見を活かして、日本での Waymo のオペレーションに影響する課題を特定し、優先順位付けを行います。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Have / 必須条件&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor of Science in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related technical degree / 工学、コンピュータ サイエンス、または関連する技術分野の学士号&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of engineering or other technical experience in automotive or another transportation field. / 自動車またはその他の輸送分野における 10 年以上のエンジニアリングまたはその他の技術分野での経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Japan’s automotive and/or transportation regulatory framework and familiarity with expectations when working with these regulators. / 日本の自動車および / または運輸分野の規制の枠組みに関する経験、ならびにこれらの規制当局と連携する際の期待事項への理解&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and presentation skills in Japanese and the ability to establish and maintain professional presence with regulators in Japan. / 日本語での優れたコミュニケーション能力およびプレゼンテーション能力、ならびに日本の規制当局との専門的な関係を確立し維持できる能力&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative mindset and the ability to work effectively with Policy, Legal, Operations, Engineering and other internal teams in Japan and in the United States. / 協調的な姿勢を有し、日本および米国のポリシー、法務、オペレーション、エンジニアリングなどの社内チームと効果的に連携できる能力&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Prefer /&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;歓迎条件&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;M.S. or Ph.D. in engineering or a related technical field / 工学または関連する技術分野の修士号または博士号&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience interacting with automotive and traffic safety regulators. / 自動車および交通安全規制当局とのやり取りの経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with autonomous vehicle technology / 自動運転技術に関する知識&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a fast-paced, rapidly-scaling company / 急速に成長しているスピード感のある企業での勤務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Travel requirements / &amp;nbsp;出張要件&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 20% travel (Domestic &amp;amp; International) / 約 20% の出張（国内および海外）&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our Driver may be autonomous, but Waymo&#39;s finances are steered by experts like you. The Finance and Accounting group manages all aspects of our finances and serves as trusted advisors for all our strategic and enterprise endeavors. Along with managing compilation of our financial statements, looking after our cash and overseeing compliance, we partner closely with the business in overseeing company wide resource allocation, developing cutting edge compensation initiatives and generating detailed financial analyses to drive the business forward. We also develop advanced capital strategies to support the company&#39;s short- and long-term future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to the Head of Finance Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish the roadmap and critical path for establishing financial operations in new international markets, ensuring regulatory compliance and managing cross-functional dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive high-stakes financial infrastructure projects from conception to launch, ensuring operational readiness and cross-functional alignment across the enterprise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect a repeatable framework to scale global corporate functions in international markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the central lead for entity setup and ongoing health; partner with Tax, Treasury, Legal, HR and International Controllership to maintain statutory and regulatory compliance as business strategies and global standards evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align local requirements with global SAP S/4HANA capabilities in collaboration with Business Systems; partner with governance teams to ensure COA structures support robust reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate to identify and mitigate operational, regulatory, and trade risks; leverage past experience to navigate common roadblocks and partner with experts to solve novel global challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 10 years of progressive experience in Finance, Accounting, or Business Enablement with a bachelor&#39;s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience leading large-scale, cross-functional transformation programs (e.g., ERP rollouts, M&amp;amp;A integrations, or new market entries) across Legal, Tax, Treasury, HR/Employment, and Finance Systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to lead effective, outcome-driven meetings with cross-functional and executive stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience collaborating with international teams and diverse stakeholder groups including the executive team, navigating cross-cultural nuances and complex, matrixed organizational structures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of US GAAP/IFRS and experience aligning business requirements with tier-one ERP capabilities (SAP preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to navigate high-ambiguity environments and shifting priorities. You are a proactive problem-solver who synthesizes data into actionable insights to overcome roadblocks, deliver results, and maintain clarity under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA, PMP, or equivalent professional certification (e.g., Change Management certification)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading process optimization projects utilizing financial technologies (RPA, AI/ML in finance)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with multiple statutory reporting frameworks (e.g., multiple country GAAP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working directly with Tax, Treasury and Legal teams on complex structural entity setups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$190,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$241,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes inclusivity and celebration. We value diverse backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences; recognize that inclusive actions lead to equitable outcomes; and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Market Fleet Readiness Across a Portfolio of Emerging Markets: Ensure the Waymo fleet is ready for service and align with performance goals and standards for the markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and Support Diagnostic Technicians: Guide and manage a team of diagnostic technicians, setting priorities and ensuring effective task execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Vendor Support and Accountability: Provide daily support to vendors, ensuring compliance with operational standards and driving accountability for performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Fleet Health and Readiness: Implement strategies to keep the fleet healthy and ready for Ride-Hail services, proactively identifying and resolving issues with internal and external teams and vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor Fleet Health and Implement Corrective Actions: Collaborate with diagnostic technicians and monitor fleet health, implement necessary corrective actions, and support vendor operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure Operational Efficiency and Reporting: Maintain consistent adherence to established processes and provide performance updates and insights to Fleet Manager and Head of Global Fleet Readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in a commercial operations and logistics role with a focus on fleet readiness initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to drive the execution of daily operational tasks, while ensuring operational efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in managing multiple projects simultaneously while ensuring timely delivery and quality outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams, external partners and executives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical skills with the ability to interpret data to identify gaps and make informed decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relationship Building: Ability to build and manage relationships, engage in-person, and foster cross-functional communication and alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coaching &amp;amp; Leadership: Strong leadership skills with the ability to clearly communicate vision, set objectives, and provide timely guidance to enhance team knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Decision-Making: Skilled in analytical and critical thinking, problem-solving, risk assessment, management, and long-term planning and prioritization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive Problem Solving: Expertise in proactively identifying potential challenges, planning remediation steps, and developing risk mitigation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vision &amp;amp; Values: Capability to lead and manage by setting and communicating a clear vision, inspiring teams, and aligning the team to organizational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel Requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 50% - This role will be responsible for a regional portfolio of Emerging Markets. Travel will be dependent on market performance and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
