&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hardware Engineering is a diverse, innovative, and collaborative group of electrical, mechanical, reliability, software and vehicle engineers. Our team builds the products which are the eyes and ears of Waymo&#39;s autonomous driving technology, and integrate those products into vehicle platforms.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to an Engineering Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create functional test specification and requirements for electronic modules and hardware used in Autonomous Vehicle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop and maintain HW/SW of test stations for PCBA&amp;nbsp; and module level testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop product troubleshooting and rework procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Contract manufacturer to integrate testers on manufacturing line and train their test teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross functional team of Electrical Engineers, Software Engineers, Production test engineers, PM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical leadership to our manufacturing partners and test equipment vendors to bring up, troubleshoot and maintain production testers and tester fixture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS or MS degree in Electrical Engineering or Computer Science&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience designing and developing Automated Test Equipments for Low Voltage electronics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on experience testing Electronic products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in Linux and developing software in Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Compute, Laser, Radar &amp;amp; Camera Technologies plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Contract Manufacturer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Python software development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in Linux networking and network infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in managing contract manufacturers, particularly in Asia, and ability to travel domestically and internationally up to 10% of the time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in Python software development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in digital and analog circuit design/analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
