&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Head of Portfolio Strategy and Value realization&lt;/strong&gt; you will serve as a strategic engine for the DTS organization. This is a high-impact leadership role responsible for the governance, financial health, and execution excellence of our entire enterprise application ecosystem. You will bridge the gap between technical delivery and business value, ensuring that our investments in SaaS Applications (ServiceNow, Salesforce, SAP), BI, and Artificial Intelligence translate into measurable competitive advantages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You are not just a &quot;project tracker&quot;; you are a &lt;strong&gt;playbook builder&lt;/strong&gt; and a &lt;strong&gt;value architect&lt;/strong&gt; who ensures we spend our capital wisely, manage our partners rigorously, and deploy AI with purpose.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, As Head of Portfolio Strategy and Value realization you will be reporting to the Head of Global IT, AI and Digital Transformation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual Strategic Planning: Architect and lead the annual strategic portfolio for the Digital Transformation team, spearheading the intake process and cross-functional prioritization with stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate the &quot;Story of Value&quot;: Regularly present to executive stakeholders on how IT spend translates into tangible business benefits and ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI Program Leadership: Lead the governance framework for AI programs to drive operational efficiency and move initiatives from experimental to production-grade.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Playbook Development: Define and institutionalize standardized playbooks for the project lifecycle, from intake to production, to enable organizational scaling and change management strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery Excellence: Oversee the global portfolio of projects across all functions to ensure on-time and on-budget delivery and implement Service realization framework clearly demonstrating the business value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vendor &amp;amp; Financial Management: Manage the lifecycle of SaaS vendors, leading high-stakes negotiations and owning the budget for the portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;15+ years of experience in IT Program Management, Portfolio Governance, or Business Technology, with at least 5 years in a senior leadership capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record managing large-scale implementations of enterprise SaaS (Salesforce, ServiceNow, or Workday) and complex ERP migrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience leading AI/ML initiatives and BI programs, with an understanding of the data lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level experience in budget management, TCO (Total Cost of Ownership) analysis, and vendor contract negotiation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elite stakeholder management skills; ability to distill complex technical updates into executive-level &quot;value stories.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates with Change management with large scale transformation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managed Enterprise SAAS and AI knowledge and experience for Program management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive stakeholders buy ins and facilitate high stake prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$238,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$302,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Waymo Insurance, you will work on the cutting edge of emerging risk and related issues surrounding our transformational autonomous driving technology and help drive our business lines forward from technology ideation through scaled commercial deployment. We partner with our legal, public policy, safety, security and privacy experts to evaluate and manage risks for the autonomous driving world to come, advising on insurance trends, evaluating and quantifying product liability, auto, cyber and related risks to ensure we build the appropriate risk and insurance frameworks to support and protect our users around the world. We collaborate with our business development, product partnership, strategy and operations teams in the execution of our business plans to ensure the company&#39;s interests are well protected from existing, new and emerging risks. We support the legal, policy and regulatory teams as they optimize our exposure in line with our risk appetite through the review of contracts, evaluation and shaping of emerging law and regulation at both the state and federal level. And we anticipate, quantify and mitigate emerging risk by maintaining active relationships and frequent contact with insurance and AV industry partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report into our Head of Risk &amp;amp; Insurance. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop Actuarial Infrastructure: Build and scale the foundational actuarial infrastructure and data systems required to support the full portfolio of Waymo&#39;s risk exposures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Management Reporting: Establish robust management reporting frameworks to communicate risk insights, portfolio performance, and actuarial findings to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Strategic Risk Advisory Efforts: Serve as a trusted advisor to senior business functions, providing guidance on risk tolerance and balance sheet protection strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate Safety Methodologies: Collaborate with internal teams to drive the development of groundbreaking actuarial methodologies to identify outsized risks and quantify the safety performance of the Waymo Driver compared to human benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Advanced Modeling: Own the outcomes for complex pricing and reserving models that quantify Waymo&#39;s expected losses and support insurance program negotiations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish Enterprise Risk Modeling Capabilities: Lead initiatives to quantify enterprise-level risks, providing senior management with a strategic framework for risk prioritization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence Industry &amp;amp; Regulatory Standards: Represent Waymo in engagements, if needed, regarding regulatory outcomes for autonomous vehicle (AV) insurance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Mastery: High technical acumen and a strong mastery of statistics and actuarial science.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Quantitative Background: An advanced degree in statistics, math, engineering or actuarial science with a mastery of both technical and business contexts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional Credentials: FCAS (Fellow of the Casualty Actuarial Society) or a PhD in a quantitative field is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven Leadership in Ambiguity: A track record of solving large, open-ended problems and driving outcomes for projects where the high-level nature of the solution was previously unclear.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive Communication Skills: Excellent collaboration and communication skills, with a demonstrated ability to present complex actuarial findings and strategic insights to very senior audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Influence: Ability to lead persuasively across senior stakeholders while reflecting diverse needs, concerns, and business interests into project deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep Casualty Expertise: Extensive experience in pricing and reserving for commercial auto lines and novel risk exposures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD: A PhD in Statistics, Mathematics, Actuarial Science, or a related highly quantitative field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ERM/CERA Designation: Specialized background in Enterprise Risk Management or a CERA (Chartered Enterprise Risk Analyst) designation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovative Problem Solving: A demonstrated ability to develop creative solutions for vague problems in a rapidly evolving technological landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$268,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$340,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our cars may be self-driving, but Waymo’s dynamic working environment is steered by experts like you.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;As our Head of Workplace Strategy and Services&amp;nbsp;you will be responsible for the delivery of large-scale operations and portfolio-wide programs ensuring and facilitating the successful delivery of a consistent service program in an extremely fast paced environment with a high degree of ambiguity. You will ensure seamless delivery of workplace strategy, headcount planning, user experience, lab management, and company-wide events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role reports to our Director of Global Workplace &amp;amp; eMobility&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occupancy Planning: Architect and execute a multi-year global workplace strategy that serves as a physical manifestation of Waymo’s safety-first and innovation-led mission, directly supporting engineering teams (hardware &amp;amp; software). Establish global Service Level Agreements (SLAs) and KPIs that utilize workplace analytics to predict trends, optimize specialized space utilization (labs, depots, and offices), and justify infrastructure investments to executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizational Scaling: Lead, scale, and inspire a global multidisciplinary organization. Foster a high-performance culture by mentoring senior leads and building a talent pipeline capable of navigating the complexities of growing offices, proving grounds, and lab infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Change Management &amp;amp; Cultural Stewardship: Act as a primary steward of Waymo’s culture, leveraging the workplace as a strategic tool to drive employee retention, talent acquisition, Employee Resource programs and cross-functional agility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portfolio-Wide Financial Oversight: Direct a multi-million dollar OPEX/CAPEX budget with a focus on Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) and rigorous ROI analysis, ensuring workplace investments yield measurable gains in engineering velocity and operational uptime.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Future-Proofing &amp;amp; Tech Integration: Pioneer the adoption of emerging workplace technologies and sustainable practices (ir Building Automation, Call Center Strategies), ensuring Waymo’s physical environments are as advanced and efficient as the autonomous technology we deploy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS degree in related field such as Facilities Management, Business Management, or Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ Years of Account Management or Outsourcing Management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills, ability to present in a formal setting, and ability to adapt communication to articulate program goals to a wide audience in a simple, straightforward way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand technological advances, change management, organizational leadership and compliance requirements, and each supports/drives workplace strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Prefer:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification or Industry Designation in Project, Engineering or Facilities Services&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in mixed use environments - office, industrial, labs or manufacturing&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable PM skills; able to advance projects with undefined scope, influence and align stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role requires travel approximately 35% of the time. Specifically, the employee will be expected to travel between Bay Area and Washington DC locations as part of their job responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
