&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the international ERT framework: &lt;/strong&gt;Create scalable standards, workflows, and readiness criteria for new markets. Conduct international market deep dives, gathering operational, regulatory, and cultural insights that shape ERT launch design. Maintain a centralized repository of international ERT standards, ensuring all stakeholders operate from a single source of truth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design localized event‑response protocols:&lt;/strong&gt; Adapt ERT procedures to reflect country-specific regulations, emergency‑services structures, and cultural expectations. Convert international compliance needs into clear, actionable ERT procedures and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop global onboarding standards:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop vendor onboarding strategy and standards, including development of training guides, documentation, and launch content to prepare vendor teams for international operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create market‑ready playbooks: &lt;/strong&gt;Define escalation paths, communication flows, and incident‑handling expectations tailored to each region. Convert international compliance needs into clear, actionable ERT procedures and documentation. Analyze learnings from pre‑launch exercises to refine protocols, documentation, and readiness recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive cross‑functional alignment:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with internal teams to integrate regulatory and public‑safety requirements into ERT processes and ensure ERT considerations are incorporated into launch timelines, dependencies, and risk mitigation. Deliver structured briefings to leadership, summarizing launch progress, risks, and decisions needed to advance market readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in operations, international expansion, public‑safety programs, regulatory readiness, or similar high‑stakes environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to build or scale programs across multiple international markets with complex regulatory landscapes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong cross‑functional collaboration skills, with experience aligning Legal, Policy, Safety, and Operations teams toward launch outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven aptitude for simplifying ambiguity through structured processes, clear documentation, and operational frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and stakeholder‑engagement skills, with the ability to influence at all levels, from working teams to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience in a Global Security Operations Center (GSOC), 911 dispatch, or live crisis command center&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some Autonomous vehicle or rideshare experience will be nice-to-have&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previously sourced, contracted, or directly managed Business Process Outsourcing (BPO) partners or other&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role is expected to travel approximately 50%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level.&amp;nbsp; Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;£103,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;£108,000 GBP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Product Operations Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure launch milestones and dependencies, assign roles and responsibilities, and establish communication channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with internal stakeholders to meet critical timelines and exceed Waymo new market launch standards to achieve operational success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep dive existing standards and processes to identify defects or improvement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify, reduce and communicate business-critical risks and dependencies to leadership and relevant stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong partnerships across the company, ensuring alignment with organizational and safety standards, goals, and a shared commitment to success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize AV software deployment process and framework for maximum efficacy of new and simultaneous launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in project management, operations management or program management at a&amp;nbsp; high-growth tech company .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously while ensuring timely delivery and quality outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with operational support for product and software launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to provide clear, strategic leadership and make quick decisions in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with quality control processes and documentation is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in risk and change management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 10%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$159,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$196,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Waymo Operations は、Waymo Driver を世界に届けるための存在です。私たちは、世界初かつ最先端の自律走行車両および運用プラットフォームを構築し、拡大するグローバル チームです。部品調達からエンド カスタマー管理まで、Waymo Driver の大規模かつオーケストレーションされた展開を通じて Waymo の価値を実現し、創造します。Waymo は、協働と称賛を促進する文化の構築に注力しています。チームメンバーの独自の背景、視点、経験を重視し、Waymo が事業を展開するコミュニティにさらに貢献できるよう、すべてのチームメンバーによるアイデアの共有をサポートし、奨励しています。Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;フリート開発およびサービス品質責任者&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;の直属として、こうしたハイブリッドな役割を担っていただきます。&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to Head of Fleet Development &amp;amp; Service Quality.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will: 業務内容&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Leverage in-depth knowledge and troubleshooting expertise to address complex issues outside of documented standard operating procedures. Engage with Waymo Engineering teams and OEM partners to resolve concerns;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;技術エキスパートとして主導的役割を果たす:&lt;/strong&gt; 豊富な知識とトラブルシューティングの専門知識を活用して、標準操作手順で規定されていない複雑な問題に対処します。Waymo エンジニアリング チームおよび相手先ブランド製造パートナーと協力し、懸念事項を解決します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimize vehicle downtime by managing escalations from partner technicians facing novel or complex issues. Guide these diagnostics remotely and in-person; &lt;strong&gt;パートナー サポートを提供する:&lt;/strong&gt; 新たな問題や複雑な問題に直面しているパートナー技術者からのエスカレーションに対応し、車両のダウンタイムを最小限に抑えます。リモートと対面の両方で問題の診断をサポートします。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct on-the-job training (including train-the-trainer) to fleet service teams as a certified instructor. Assist in the continuous development of training content; &lt;strong&gt;トレーニングの実施と開発を行う:&lt;/strong&gt; 認定インストラクターとして、フリート サービス チームへの実地研修（トレーナーのトレーニングを含む）を実施します。また、トレーニング コンテンツの継続的な開発を支援します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure market adherence to service and quality assurance standards that drive safety and consistency. Conduct regular audits and assessments to verify compliance;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;品質基準を維持する:&lt;/strong&gt; 安全性と一貫性を推進するサービスおよび品質保証基準が市場で確実に遵守されるようにします。コンプライアンスを確認するために定期的な監査と評価を実施します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering teams to identify and address potential issues before they impact fleet uptime. Perform analysis that identifies high value diagnostic development opportunities;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;技術知識を文書化する:&lt;/strong&gt; フリート サービス チームをサポートするための技術ドキュメント、トラブルシューティング ガイド、操作手順、ベスト プラクティスを開発および管理します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain technical documentation, troubleshooting guides, operating procedures, and best practices to support fleet service teams; &lt;strong&gt;リスクと機会を積極的に特定する:&lt;/strong&gt; エンジニアリング チームと連携して、フリートの稼働時間に影響が出る前に潜在的な問題を特定し、対処します。また、価値の高い診断開発の機会を特定するための分析を実施します。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have: 必須条件:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingual - competent speaking and writing both Japanese and English; バイリンガル - 日本語と英語の両方で会話と文章作成が可能な方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience in an automotive technician or automotive engineering role;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;自動車整備士または自動車エンジニアリング職で 5 年以上の経験を有している方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mastery of automotive diagnostic strategies, service methods, and tools covering electrical, including high voltage powertrains, mechanical, and networking (e.g. CAN),&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;自動車診断戦略、サービス手法、および電気系（高電圧パワートレインを含む）、機械系、ネットワーク系（例: コントローラ エリア ネットワーク）を網羅するツールを習得されている方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in managing multiple projects simultaneously while ensuring timely delivery and quality outcomes,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;複数のプロジェクトを同時に管理し、期限内に質の高い成果を収めた実績がある方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal, written, and interpersonal communication skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams, external partners, and executives; 口頭や文章で意思疎通を図る能力、および対人コミュニケーション能力に優れ、部門横断型チーム、外部パートナー、経営陣と効果的に連携できる方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical skills to identify developmental opportunities and communicate them effectively, 成長機会を特定し、効果的に伝える分析能力を有している方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer: 歓迎条件:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Class 1 national auto mechanic license; 1 級自動車整備士の国家資格をお持ちの方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building or servicing autonomous vehicles or technology; 自動運転車または自動運転技術の開発経験または整備経験がある方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience administering technical training; 技術研修の実施経験がある方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing, improving, and deploying operational processes using change management best practices;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;チェンジ マネジメントのベスト プラクティスを使用して運用プロセスを設計、改善、導入した経験がある方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with technical writing and technical documentation; テクニカル ライティングおよび技術ドキュメントを作成した経験がある方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with fleet operations or fleet management principles; フリート オペレーションまたはフリート管理の原則に関する知識をお持ちの方&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;出張要件&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;フリートのニーズに対応するため、急な出張にも柔軟に対応できる方 - 出張は勤務時間の最大 20% になる可能性があります。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Waymo Operations exists to deliver the Waymo Driver to the world. We are a global team building and scaling the world&#39;s first and leading autonomous fleet and operations platform. From component sourcing to end customer management, we enable and create value for Waymo through scaled and orchestrated deployment of the Waymo Driver. At Waymo, we are dedicated to building a culture that promotes collaboration and celebration. We value our team members&#39; unique backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences and support and encourage all team members to share their ideas to help Waymo better serve the communities in which we operate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to the Head of Waymo Training and Documentation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead the localization and internationalization strategy&lt;/strong&gt; for all of Waymo Operations, ensuring all Internal documentation and training is culturally and operationally relevant across global regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive nomenclature standardization&lt;/strong&gt; across various regions and Lines of Business (LOBs) to ensure operational consistency while respecting local nuances and regulatory requirements.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project manage the end-to-end translation and localization lifecycle&lt;/strong&gt; for hundreds of technical artifacts, acting as the primary point of person for content parity between training materials and&amp;nbsp; Internal Knowledge Base (IKB).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set the roadmap for global expansion&lt;/strong&gt; by ensuring all documentation is &quot;market-ready,&quot; enabling new regions to achieve successful launches with high learning proficiency and safety outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally&lt;/strong&gt; with product, legal, and regional ops teams to ensure that localized content meets the specific safety-critical and regulatory needs of each unique market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the quality and integrity&lt;/strong&gt; of translated technical content, ensuring that &quot;translation&quot; never comes at the expense of technical accuracy or safety compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8+ years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; in localization, internationalization, or technical project management, specifically within complex operational or fleet environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage high-volume documentation portfolios&lt;/strong&gt; (100+ assets) across multiple regions, with a focus on maintaining version control and content parity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expert knowledge of localization tools (TMS) and methodologies&lt;/strong&gt;, with a deep understanding of how to adapt technical SOPs and IKBs for international audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful track record of leading large-scale projects&lt;/strong&gt; in high-pace environments where business-critical deadlines and high volumes of change are the norm.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong expertise in managing global vendors&lt;/strong&gt; and extended workforces to deliver high-quality localized content within budget and on schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced understanding of &quot;Internationalization vs. Localization&quot; principles&lt;/strong&gt;, specifically regarding how to build &quot;global-first&quot; documentation templates that reduce future translation friction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience in workflow optimization&lt;/strong&gt; and process excellence, specifically in automating the hand-off between content creators and localization teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Familiarity with safety-critical operations&lt;/strong&gt; where precise nomenclature and clear instructions are vital to risk mitigation and regulatory adherence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Travel requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10-15% travel required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$159,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$202,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Simulator Team at Waymo builds state-of-the-art simulations of realistic environments for testing and training the Waymo Driver. Our team is a diverse and collaborative group of software engineers, machine learning (ML) engineers, and data scientists. We develop industry-leading simulation solutions using advanced ML algorithms that measure and enhance the performance of the Waymo Driver. By applying machine learning, we model the real world, including realistic agents (vehicles, pedestrians, cyclists, motorcyclists), roads, traffic control systems, and weather conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To increase the fidelity and steerability of our simulations, we employ the latest ML technologies such as large foundational World Model trained on our datasets, world understanding and reasoning capabilities for tail cases, and reinforcement learning for long term credit assignment. We also invest in capable infrastructure that allows us to quickly set up and roll out multiple counterfactual scenarios to rigorously test our autonomous driving systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Senior Staff Tech Lead Manager&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive innovation in ultra-realistic world simulation for autonomous vehicles. You will develop the latest simulation technologies using foundation models for embodied agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply your deep Machine Learning (ML) expertise, in Generative AI (GenAI), to push the boundaries of simulation realism and directly influence the advancement of autonomous driving technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Waymo&#39;s foundational AI research team to transfer research into scalable and production-ready solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience with ML software engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience with Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of ML software experience with machine learning framework including Pytorch, Tensorflow, Jax/Flax ,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with, creating and/or developing ML models for robotics and/or self driving vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong C++ in production setting, with experience in integrating ML models in production system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in training large scale models on GPU/TPU clusters are strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
