&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Depot UX team is seeking a visionary engineer to build the tools that empower our enterprise partners to manage, maintain, and scale our vehicles globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team focuses on creating solutions for Commercial RO Managers and depot field operators. Their core mission is to revolutionize depot operations by delivering intuitive and efficient user experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will design, own, and deploy a suite of mission-critical mobile and web applications—the unseen intelligence guiding everything from vehicle readiness and complex servicing protocols to real-time fleet visualization. This is your chance to architect the operational future of autonomous transportation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to an Engineering Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build Android systems critical to Waymo&#39;s success, such as:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create Android components and flows using modern Android technologies such as Jetpack Compose.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The application used by enterprise partners to manage their fleets of autonomous vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational libraries, including scalable UI components, architecture &amp;amp; performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solve hard, real-world problems, such as:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve human task completion by depot operators; encapsulate the complexity of autonomous fleet management and make it accessible to partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and create infrastructure to enhance app scalability and developer productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members such as product managers, designers, fleet operations, and UX researchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join the team owning a couple of tools used by enterprise partners: Android applications and web app application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS/MS degree in Computer Science or related technical field or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience building UX designs on the Android platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on medium to large-scale Android apps involving multiple developers and designers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Kotlin, Java, Android applications and UIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Jetpack Compose in a production environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated passion and substantial experience in crafting user-facing products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adept at collaborating with product designers to achieve pixel-perfect UI implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Server Driven UI (SDUI) paradigms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing experience with or a demonstrated openness to embracing mobile full-stack development. Our team encompasses ownership of both the client-side (Android or Angular web-app) and the specialized “mobile backend for frontend” component (implemented in Kotlin).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo&#39;s commercial service is running in five cities, and the associated infrastructure is in an early stage and requires investment for Waymo to grow into a high scale, world-class service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building a team of engineers dedicated to further developing our Android Platform team. Our team works on the user interfaces used by customers to interact with our autonomous vehicles as well as provide entertainment and information while riding. This is a fullstack team, managing the bring up and maintenance of a complete automotive grade Android system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to an Engineering Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate SoC vendor development kits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop update mechanism for Android OS and applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with vendors, HW team and other stakeholders to define requirements for next UX platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring up Android on new hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical support for other teams working on our Android devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS/MS degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of software development experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with low-level Android/AOSP (building Android platform features, frameworks), not just developing apps on top of Android&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Worked with git, repo and gerrit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brought up Android on new hardware, or customized a build of Android for a new hardware variant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with security aspects of Android, SELinux and key provisioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$170,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$216,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Perception team builds the system which learns the spatial-temporal representation and their semantic meanings of the surrounding environment of the autonomously driving vehicle (ADV), i.e., the system that “perceives” the world around the car. We work jointly with downstream teams on the optimization and integration into the Waymo Driver. We conduct our own research to address real-world problems and collaborate with research teams at Alphabet. We have access to millions of miles of driving data from a diverse set of sensors, enabling engineers like you to (1) develop methods for efficiently and continuously learning from large scale real-world data, to (2) develop models and model training at scale, to (3) analyze real-world behavior and develop systems for handling the complexities of interacting with the real-world, and (4) optimize models for our onboard and offboard hardware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role you will report to a Technical Lead Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own tasks in the ML Driver, take responsibility for task scaling and task performance, create ML methods and recipes to scale and improve tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze behavior of ML systems in real-world application, identify issues and root causes, advise or develop short- and long-term solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor ML systems in production, develop methods for automatically detecting issues or regressions, develop AI-aided analysis and debugging tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain metrics for ADV relevant issues, including safety-critical and longtail issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors in Computer Science or a similar discipline, or an equivalent amount of deep learning experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years experience in Machine Learning and Computer Vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with ML frameworks like PyTorch or JAX&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MS or PhD Degree in Machine Learning, Robotics, Computer Science or a similar discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Publications at top-tier conferences like CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, ICLR, ICML, ICRA, IROS, RSS, NeurIPS, AAAI, IJCV, PAMI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with C++&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$204,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$259,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Design at Waymo is about the total experience, not just how the product looks, but how it works, how it feels, and how we make our new technology accessible, approachable, and useful for everyone. We design the intuitive, delightful experience for our riders, and we also build the powerful, complex tools used by our fleet operations teams and the engineers who build the Waymo Driver. We are a highly multidisciplinary team of UX Designers, User and Market Researchers, UX Engineers, Content Designers, Industrial Designers, CAD Designers, Studio Engineers, and Technical Artists. We dig deep to understand the attitudes, emotions, and behaviors of all our users. This understanding serves as the foundation for everything we create.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role follows a hybrid work schedule and you will report to a Studio Engineering Manager.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development of high-quality 3D CAD models from initial concept sketches and Industrial Design proposals through to final, production-intent Class-A surfaces. Utilize appropriate fidelity CAD design processes to drive efficient design development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Industrial Designers, Hardware Engineers, and Manufacturing teams to translate design intent into feasible, high-quality surfaces that meet all product and engineering requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support preparation of appropriate CAD files for 3D visualization, and manage digital and physical prototyping workflows (e.g., 3D printing, CNC) to verify form, function, and assembly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and solve complex surfacing and geometry challenges, navigating technical constraints while upholding the highest standards of design quality and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional automotive experience as a CAD Designer, 3D Modeler, or Digital Sculptor in a product-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level proficiency in Class-A surfacing tools using Alias. Strong understanding of quality CAD building strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of delivering high-quality 3D data for mass production, with a deep understanding of manufacturing processes, materials, and assemblies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong portfolio demonstrating exceptional technical skill, meticulous attention to detail, and successfully shipped products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A degree in Industrial Design, Transportation Design, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing for complex, integrated hardware systems (e.g., robotics, aerospace, advanced consumer electronics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with CNC programming, advanced 3D printing, or other rapid prototyping methods. Experience working with model shops to create looks-like, feels-like model assets like marketing show cars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel Requirements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 times a quarter (less than 15%)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$196,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$248,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As part of Waymo&#39;s Legal team, you will work on the exciting legal issues surrounding our transformational autonomous driving technology and help drive our business lines forward from technology ideation through scaled commercial deployment.&amp;nbsp; We partner with our public policy, safety, security and privacy experts to define transportation policy for the autonomous driving world to come, advising on regulatory changes that support and protect our users around the world.&amp;nbsp; We collaborate with our engineering, product, strategy and operations teams to develop and protect our intellectual property portfolio and drive our corporate and commercial transactions. We ensure compliance with an increasingly complex and dynamic range of global regulations. And we anticipate, mitigate, and litigate high-profile and precedent-setting legal matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Waymo の法務チームの一員として、Waymo の革新的な自動運転技術をめぐる法的問題に取り組み、技術構想から大規模な商用展開まで、各事業ラインを牽引していただきます。Waymo は公共政策、安全、セキュリティ、プライバシーの専門家と提携して、自動運転における交通政策を定義するとともに、世界中のユーザーをサポートし保護するための規制改正について提言を行います。また、エンジニアリングやプロダクト、戦略、運用の各チームと協力して、知的財産ポートフォリオの構築および保護、企業間、商取引の推進を担います。複雑化し、変化し続けるグローバルな規制へのコンプライアンスを確実なものとし、注目度が高く先例となるような法的案件を予見および軽減し、訴訟対応を通じて解決へと導きます。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role you will report directly to our Managing Counsel.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;こうしたハイブリッドな職責を担う業務内容は以下のとおりです。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will / 業務内容:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as lead attorney on a wide range of Japan and greater APAC related projects, and provide the full range of supporting legal services to other global Legal teams, including commercial deals, advocacy, event response, employment, and dispute resolution, in support of Waymo’s success in the region. / 日本および広域アジア太平洋地域の主任弁護士として、関連する幅広いプロジェクトを統括する。同地域における Waymo の成功をサポートするため、商取引、アドボカシー、イベント事案、雇用、紛争解決など、他のグローバル法務チームに包括的な法的サービスを提供する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic guidance to key cross-functional internal stakeholders on a wide range of legal, business, corporate strategy and governance issues relevant to Japan and the greater APAC region. / 日本および広域アジア太平洋地域に関連する法務、ビジネス、経営戦略、ガバナンスの広範な論点について、社内の主要な部門横断的なステークホルダーに戦略的ガイダンスを提示する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with key partners such as public policy, public affairs, product counsels, regulatory counsels, communications, compliance and others to jointly develop and implement winning strategies, including representing Waymo in interactions with local agencies and organizations as required. / 公共政策、広報、プロダクト担当顧問、規制担当顧問、コミュニケーション、コンプライアンスなどの主要なパートナーと緊密に連携する。「勝てる戦略」を共同で策定、実行し、必要に応じて現地の行政機関や団体との折衝において Waymo を代理する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support cross-functional global teams with navigating country/region specific laws and regulations, including&amp;nbsp; coordinating internally and externally to closely monitor, review, report on, and shape changing laws and regulations in Japan and the greater APAC region relevant to Waymo’s business. / 社内外の調整を通じて、日本および広域アジア太平洋地域における Waymo の事業に関連する法規制の動向を綿密に注視、把握、報告、形成することで、グローバルチームが各国の固有法や規制を遵守できるようサポートを行う。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain subject matter expertise in new areas as novel regional issues and topics emerge. / 地域の新たな課題やトピックの発生にあわせて、新しい領域の専門知識を習得する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compliance and other corporate governance tasks related to Japan and the greater APAC region. / 日本および広域アジア太平洋地域におけるコンプライアンス維持、およびその他のコーポレート ガバナンス業務を支援する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have / 必要な条件/経験:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Law degree (LLB, LLM or JD) / 法学の学位（LLB、LLM、または JD）&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Admitted to practice law in Japan / 日本における弁護士資格&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 8 years of experience practicing law, 4 of which involve practicing law in Japan / 8 年以上の法務実務経験。うち 4 年は日本国内での実務に従事していること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience assisting international technology companies with introducing novel products and services into Japan and other APAC countries / 国際的なテック企業において、日本および広域アジア太平洋地域への新製品やサービスの導入を支援した経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience engaging Japanese and other APAC regulators on a range of topics / 多岐にわたるテーマにおいて、日本および広域アジア太平洋地域の規制当局と交渉した経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in Japanese and English / 日本語と英語が堪能であること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer / 望ましい経験/スキル:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in the automotive industry or ride-hailing industry / 自動車業界または配車サービス業界での実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working as an in house counsel / 社内弁護士としての実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additionally admitted to practice law in another country&amp;nbsp; / 日本以外の国において弁護士活動の認可を取得していること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in one or more additional languages spoken in the APAC region / アジア太平洋地域で使用されている言語（ 1 つ以上）に堪能であること&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 15 years of experience practicing law / 15 年以上の法務実務経験&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience working with international legal teams and clients / グローバルな法務チームやクライアントと連携し、成果を上げた実績&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel Requirements / 出張について&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel required, primarily within APAC and occasionally to the US / 出張が発生します（主にアジア太平洋地域内、必要に応じて米国）&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

