&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$204,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$259,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;The Waymo Safety team works to promote and help to continuously improve the safety of Waymo’s fully autonomous driving technology. Our experts develop safety goals and strategies, and conduct safety engineering analyses to ensure safety is being considered throughout the design and development of our vehicles. The team develops and promotes safety strategies and policies for autonomous vehicles for its work with regulatory authorities, lawmakers, law enforcement and public and non-profit organizations. Our Safety Team also helps advise on compliance with applicable environmental, health, and safety regulations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to a Environment, Health and Safety Manager.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement a comprehensive EHS management system for Waymo&#39;s EMEA operations, based on Waymo’s Global EHS Standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure full compliance with all applicable local, national, and regional EHS laws and regulations by proactively tracking regulatory changes, maintaining the EHS legal register, and implementing necessary program updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively manage EHS in a workforce consisting of both employees and third-party vendors by conducting EHS assurance activities, managing EHS event response&amp;nbsp; including investigations and root cause analyses, and overseeing performance to ensure safe work practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide EHS support for Waymo&#39;s operating partners, ensuring their operations adhere to all legal requirements and Waymo&#39;s internal safety standards through regular assurance activities, training, and collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct EHS risk assessments for all Waymo work activities within the region, identifying and executing opportunities to implement improved controls to mitigate hazards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive a culture of continuous improvement by developing and monitoring key EHS performance indicators (KPIs), preparing regular reports for leadership, and championing safety initiatives across the region&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Occupational Health &amp;amp; Safety, Environmental Science, Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 7 years of progressive experience in an EHS role, with at least 3 years in a regional management capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of UK and EU EHS regulations and standards applicable to vehicle maintenance, construction, and general industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience managing EHS within operational facilities such as transportation, manufacturing, or energy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record managing safety aspects related to vendors and contractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NEBOSH National/International Diploma in Occupational Health and Safety (or an equivalent, such as an NVQ Level 6) and membership in a professional body (e.g., GradIOSH, CMIOSH).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the autonomous vehicle, automotive, or high-tech hardware industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specific expertise in the safety and environmental aspects of high-voltage systems and electric vehicle (EV) charging infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing EHS programs across multiple countries within the EMEA region, navigating diverse regulatory landscapes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with implementing and managing ISO 45001 and ISO 14001 management systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with experience using data and metrics to identify trends, measure performance, and drive EHS improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to influence and build strong relationships with external partners, contractors, and internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approximately 40% travel, with 30% within the EMEA region and 10% outside EMEA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level.&amp;nbsp; Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;£110,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;£119,000 GBP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Waymo&#39;s Compute Team is tasked with a critical and exciting mission: We deliver the compute platform responsible for running the fully autonomous vehicle’s software stack. To achieve our mission, we architect and create high-performance custom silicon; we develop system-level compute architectures that push the boundaries of performance, power, and latency; and we collaborate closely with many other teammates to ensure we design and optimize hardware and software for maximum performance. We are a multidisciplinary team seeking curious and talented teammates to work on one of the world’s highest performance automotive compute platforms. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role follows a hybrid work schedule and you will report to a Silicon Engineering Lead.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive formal strategy for first-pass silicon success. Own the formal verification sign-off approach across complex IP and SoC designs, utilizing advanced formal techniques (e.g., Bounded Model Checking, Datapath Validation, Connectivity, Sequential LEC, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect robust and scalable FV environments. Develop and deploy reusable formal testbenches, methodology flows, and high-coverage SVA assertion suites for systemic deployment across multiple design blocks and projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical leadership &amp;amp; mentorship. Serve as the team&#39;s formal Subject Matter Expert, training and guiding logic designers and verification engineers to effectively incorporate formal methods into their workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic planning and test plan execution. Collaborate with Architecture and Design teams to translate complex system and IP specifications into comprehensive formal verification test plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive FV Infrastructure &amp;amp; Reporting. Maintain and enhance continuous integration, regression flows, and dashboarding to provide clear, actionable formal verification status and sign-off metrics to leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced bug-hunting and debugging. Apply state-of-the-art formal techniques (e.g., assume-guarantee, abstractions, reductions) to tackle and efficiently decompose the most challenging, intractable verification problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS/MS/PhD in CS/EE or related field, combined with 5+ years of hands-on formal verification experience on shipping silicon products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep, expert-level proficiency with at least one major commercial formal verification platform (e.g., Cadence JasperGold, Synopsys VC Formal, Mentor Questa Formal)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level language proficiency in C++ and/or Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to model complex designs in SystemVerilog and advanced SystemVerilog Assertions, including writing complex cut-points and environment models for effective formal proof convergence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in applying advanced formal debug techniques for problem decomposition (e.g., clock domain crossings, abstractions, assume-guarantee reasoning)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to influence cross-functional teams (Design, Architecture, Software) and drive technical alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informed of latest developments in formal verification research and industry practice, identify opportunities for Waymo&#39;s silicon development process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in formally proving correctness of arithmetic units such as floating point adders and multipliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge/experience working with NOCs and networking topologies, protocols (Eg. AXI/AMBA)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand basic principles of cache coherency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with high-performance designs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The expected base salary range for this full-time position across US locations is listed below. Actual starting pay will be based on job-related factors, including exact work location, experience, relevant training and education, and skill level. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for the role location or, if the role can be performed remote, the specific salary range for your preferred location, during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Waymo employees are also eligible to participate in Waymo’s discretionary annual bonus program, equity incentive plan, and generous Company benefits program, subject to eligibility requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$204,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$259,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Want to build the next generation of infrastructure for driverless cars?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our Waymo Driver Validation team, and help us design the future of transportation! We are looking for a passionate Senior Fullstack Engineer who wants to help build the systems that improve Waymo&#39;s core ride hailing and fleet management systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are someone who is product-minded. You will work on cross-cutting problems to require cross-team collaboration, both technically (mobile app, cloud backends, and the Waymo Driver) and functionally (operations, product, legal, partnerships, policy &amp;amp; privacy) to develop and deliver business critical infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hybrid role, you will report to an Engineering Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help build and evolve mission-critical horizontal infrastructure and tooling that underpins all commercialization systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other engineering teams to develop systems and processes as business needs grow and evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale our systems to meet the demands of commercial expansion and growing complexity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solve hard, real-world problems such as world simulation for regression testing and evaluation of software services managing fleets for autonomous vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years of experience in full stack development, across back-end such as Java/Kotlin, Python, GO, or C++ codebases, and front-end experience including JavaScript or TypeScript, HTML, CSS or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of front-end web technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building data visualization and/or data management applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating with UX and Interaction design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with engineering artifacts, reliability monitoring and alerting, security and privacy practices and techniques, documentation, integration testing, production hygiene, and support processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate with other software developers and cross-functional stakeholders at multiple levels and across sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world&#39;s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World&#39;s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Waymo Expansion Tooling team, part of the TaaS organization within Waymo Commercialization, focuses on building internal tools and platforms to accelerate and streamline Waymo&#39;s geographic expansion. Our work is mission-critical to Waymo&#39;s company-level goals; it will directly enable Waymo to launch new territories, cities, and airports with more efficiency and reliability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Senior Fullstack Software Engineer to develop a suite of web tools to empower Product Managers, TPMs, and Operations teams to manage the expansion lifecycle. This includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simplifying Launches: Creating user-friendly UIs to configure service areas, assign vehicle fleets, manage access for different user groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automating Validation: Building in checks and validations to ensure all prerequisites for a launch are met, reducing the risk of errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improving Efficiency: Reducing the reliance on manual code changes for standard expansion tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;End-to-End Vision: Long-term, the team aims to build a comprehensive platform to manage the entire expansion process, from initial planning and service area creation to rolling out to riders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the first frontend engineer on this team, you will play a critical role in shaping the infrastructure and UI foundations of our expansion tooling. Your tasks will center around building web apps that are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intuitive and User-Friendly: Enabling non-engineering teams to confidently manage complex launch processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficient: Streamlining workflows and reducing the time it takes to launch new service areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informative: Clearly presenting the status of various checks, validations, and launch steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Impactful: Your work will directly contribute to Waymo&#39;s growth and ability to bring our autonomous driving technology to more people in more places.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Product Managers, Engineers, and the tool users to understand their needs and translate them into effective and elegant web designs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5+ years of professional experience in software development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expertise in building modern web applications using component-based frameworks (e.g., Angular, React, Vue)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong understanding of web development fundamentals including HTML, CSS, and modern JavaScript/TypeScript&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills and ability to collaborate effectively with diverse engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Familiarity with Java/Kotlin/C++ for backend development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working with data visualization and mapping libraries (e.g., Mapbox, Deck.gl, D3.js).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
