&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment and test planning activities with both internal and external OEM partners to ensure efficient and effective collaboration across Waymo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical support to Test Engineers and Test Conductors during the execution of the verification activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become the point of contact and be accountable for the tests requested from Systems Engineers or Developers to test new features or detect regressions for existing ones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute on test automation strategy for verification corpus which effectively utilizes Waymo&#39;s suite of test environments from software-in-loop simulation to component HILs to full vehicle HILs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical training to other Test Engineers to grow the team’s skillset. For example: use of test equipment, analysis tools, test methodologies, or scripting languages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the qualification of new Waymo driver SW releases for the Vehicle Test Engineering team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in one of the following technical domains:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thermal Management: experience with testing thermal performance of complex systems, for example using thermal chambers, windtunnels, or simulation&lt;/li&gt;
