&lt;li&gt;Perform site audits with the Service Quality team to ensure training proficiency retention while identifying opportunities for operational improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, operationalize, and maintain quality standards that drive operational consistency, reliability, and alignment with organizational goals, particularly related to partner’s training programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize training schedules across multiple partners to ensure capacity growth aligns with Waymo’s demand and partner onboarding schedules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years professional automotive service instructional or educational experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built, managed and/or maintained standard operating procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills critical for explaining complex topics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to present information confidently and effectively to groups&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to uphold the highest standards for safety and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leveraged a Learning Management System to organize, deploy, and track training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We prefer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years experience in the automotive service field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data analytics and reporting in Excel, GSheets, or SQL&lt;/li&gt;
