&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture Management &amp;amp; Promotion:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and spearhead closed-loop processes for maintaining a positive safety culture, and other internal initiatives (e.g., Safety Month, newsletters, town halls) to promote safety awareness and reinforce a positive safety culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governance Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in the management of safety committees and working groups, ensuring alignment between policy objectives and effective departmental implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a primary point of contact for internal teams to interpret safety policies and gather feedback on how to improve all aspects of the SMS and the &quot;lived&quot; safety culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goals &amp;amp; Metrics:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and track SMS-related goals and Safety Performance Indicators (SPIs) related to the SMS broadly, safety culture maturity, and policy compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
