&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive design and implementation of operational metrics, dashboards, and standardized cross-organizational reporting systems in coordination with internal and vendor analytics teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead demand forecasting, workforce and budget planning, and plan-to-actuals spend monitoring processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish foundational architecture and automated systems to enable vendor data analysts to build and maintain scalable operational reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee standardized business review frameworks and hold vendors accountable to SLAs, KPIs, and committed action plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop short and long-term project roadmaps, managing timelines, impact, and documentation for internal customers and vendor leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align with senior stakeholders on quarterly objectives, reporting on program metrics to continuously improve area effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA / BS in technical or business discipline or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years in data intelligence, statistics, or other related field with proven experience designing and implementing analytical strategies, process optimization initiatives, and technical programs for people at all levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of program management experience with large, complex projects and cross-functional stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A highly analytical mindset with demonstrated background of creating &amp;amp; defining metrics for a program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced writing concise documentation (e.g. business requirements, summary reports, project briefs), and delivering engaging presentations, often to senior leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert proficiency with Python and SQL and experience designing and implementing complex data pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
