&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience in insurance operations, claims administration, risk management, or a similar complex operational environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management Mastery:&lt;/strong&gt; Demonstrated ability to manage complex cross-functional timelines, orchestrate internal workflows, and track team objectives (OKRs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data &amp;amp; Tooling Fluency:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience guiding data and tooling projects—defining business requirements for dashboards and automation—rather than direct technical implementation (you know what to ask for, even if you don&#39;t build the SQL yourself).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience managing vendor lifecycles (contracting, onboarding, performance tracking) and critical documentation (filings, COIs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent written skills for executive reporting, with experience managing financial tracking (budgets) or Quarterly Business Review (QBR) processes.&lt;/li&gt;
